================================================================================
Ideas distilled into native Go (clean-room, NO source code used)
================================================================================

The following projects and research inspired ideas that were re-authored from
scratch in Go. No source code from them is included in or distributed with
ReadyBase. These are courtesy credits, not license obligations:

  - dependency-cruiser   (MIT)          https://github.com/sverweij/dependency-cruiser
        static dependency graph with rules written against it
  - madge                (MIT)          https://github.com/pahen/madge
        module dependency graph and circular-dependency detection
  - CodeScene / "Your Code as a Crime Scene", Adam Tornhill   (proprietary, book)
        behavioral code analysis: hotspots, change coupling, knowledge maps
  - Truck Factor research, Avelino/Passos/Hora/Valente, 2016  (research)
        estimating bus / truck factor from version-control authorship
  - GitHub CODEOWNERS    (convention)   https://docs.github.com/articles/about-code-owners
        mapping paths to the people and teams who own them
  - SonarQube            (LGPL-3.0)     https://github.com/SonarSource/sonarqube
        a composite quality gate over many independent signals
  - agents.md / Claude Code  (convention / platform)  https://agents.md
        project context files an agent reads (AGENTS.md, CLAUDE.md)

================================================================================
Third-party Go libraries compiled into the readybase binary
================================================================================

These are linked into the released binary and distributed with it:

  github.com/odvcencio/gotreesitter   (MIT)          pure-Go incremental parser,
        implementing the tree-sitter idea (https://github.com/tree-sitter/tree-sitter, MIT)
  modernc.org/sqlite                  (BSD-3-Clause)  embedded scan/history/console database
  github.com/google/uuid              (BSD-3-Clause)  identifiers for scans and records

The complete set of third-party Go modules compiled into the binary (11 modules,
resolved from `go list -deps ./cmd/readybase`) and their licenses is listed in
THIRD_PARTY_LICENSES.md. The full, verbatim text of each license is reproduced
in the LICENSES/ directory, including the golang.org/x/sys PATENTS grant and the
modernc.org/libc upstream third-party C license file.

